name: NYDailyNews
text:
No crowds, no cheering, no betting window lines.

Tiz the Law won the COVID-19 Belmont Stakes before an empty grandstand, becoming the first New York-bred horse to win the Belmont in 138 years.

text:
Fire investigators issued an arrest warrant for a suspect in the torching of an Atlanta Wendy’s.

The fast-food restaurant went up in flames a week ago, one day after a cop shot fatally shot Rayshard Brooks at the drive-thru.

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Jim Kiick, a running who helped the Miami Dolphins achieve the NFL’s only perfect season in 1972, is dead at 73.

The former University of Wyoming star was part of a formidable backfield that included his best friend, Hall of Fame fullback Larry Csonka.
https://t.co/hkUhEDJH5i

text:
Two people of interest were identified in the viral caught-on-video Michigan Macy’s attack.

The clip posted to Facebook said in the caption an employee mumbled the N-word before the man in the video began to hammer him.
